      • getShell

        public static org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell getShell()
        Returns:
        Returns a shell with current shell style being used across the application. The need arises because of the extensibility purposes. Some of the shells may be extensible.
        Note: The same shell is reused across the application. In case, the shell is disposed, or new styled shell needs to be used, a new shell is created and returned.

      • getActiveShell

        public static org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell getActiveShell()

      • getShellStyle

        public static int getShellStyle()
        Returns:
        The shell style to be used across the application.
        Note:While using the shell style with exensibility mode on, make sure that the new shell's parent is the currently active shell. Otherwise, the shell may go to the background if user clicks on the parent window.
